## Overview

I build production-grade AI systems — from retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) pipelines to real-time computer vision — that go beyond demos and actually hold up under real usage.

My core focus is RAG and LLM applications. I've designed and shipped multiple end-to-end systems covering the full pipeline: document parsing, chunking strategy, embedding, hybrid retrieval, cross-encoder reranking, and grounded LLM generation — served through FastAPI and containerized with Docker.

A few examples of what I've built:
- **NB-LLM** — a PDF knowledge base with parent-child chunking, BGE embeddings, cross-encoder reranking, semantic caching, and real-time streamed answers.
- **Doc Lens** — multi-document RAG with exact page citations, hybrid vector + full-text search (RRF fusion), and vision-LLM-generated figure descriptions, with Celery-based ingestion at scale.
- **YT-Assistant** — conversational RAG over YouTube transcripts with timestamp-linked answers and per-user data isolation via Firebase.

On the computer vision side, I've built real-time face recognition (InsightFace/ArcFace) and YOLOv8-based object detection and tracking systems with live hardware integration (gimbal cameras), which I also do professionally in my current role.

**What I bring to a project:**
- End-to-end ownership: data ingestion → retrieval → generation → API → deployment
- Practical performance tuning (latency, cost, retrieval precision) — not just "make it work," but make it work well
- Comfortable working across the modern AI stack: ChromaDB, Qdrant, PostgreSQL, Redis, sentence-transformers, OpenRouter

If you need a RAG system that actually retrieves the right context, an LLM-powered app that's grounded and reliable, or a computer vision pipeline that runs in real time — let's talk about what you're building.

